cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with wireless networking and optimization of concurrent transmissions in random access scenarios. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves statistical learning and optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed coordination architecture involves control and coordination of multiple access points, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
